  "prompt": "What are the best restaurants to try when visiting Hubbali, Karnataka, India? What should you try while you're there?",
  "response": "Hubli (also known as Hubballi) offers a variety of delicious local and regional cuisines. Here are some recommended restaurants and dishes to try:\n\nRestaurants:\n1. Hotel Suvarna Continental\n- Multi-cuisine restaurant\n- Known for North and South Indian dishes\n- Good vegetarian and non-vegetarian options\n\n2. Hotel Gurudev\n- Popular local restaurant\n- Traditional Karnataka cuisine\n- Affordable and tasty meals\n\n3. Basaveshwara Restaurant\n- Local North Karnataka specialties\n- Famous for traditional thali meals\n- Authentic regional flavors\n\n4. Hotel Pearl\n- Multi-cuisine restaurant\n- Good for family dining\n- Variety of vegetarian and non-vegetarian dishes\n\nLocal Dishes to Try:\n1. Jolada Roti (Jowar Roti)\n- Traditional North Karnataka bread\n- Made from sorghum flour\n- Often served with spicy curries\n\n2. Dharwad Peda\n- Famous local sweet\n- Originated in nearby Dharwad\n- Milk-based dessert\n\n3. Karnataka-style Bisi Bele Bath\n- Spicy rice and lentil dish\n- Mixed with vegetables\n- Regional specialty\n\n4. North Karnataka Thali\n- Complete meal with multiple dishes\n- Includes variety of curries, rice, and bread\n\nThese recommendations should help you explore Hubli's culinary landscape.",
